      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about an escrow account for the closing and i'm kinda confused. what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the house purchase?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, an escrow account, you say? Well, imagine a treasure chest guarded by a wise old goblin, who only opens it when both the buyer and seller agree on the terms of the treasure exchange. In the world of house buying, this goblin is like the escrow agent, ensuring that both parties fulfill their promises before the treasure (or house) changes hands. The escrow account holds the money, like a treasure hoard, until all the conditions are met, ensuring that neither party gets greedy and runs off with the treasure before the deal is complete. It's a way to keep the peace in the land of property transactions, wouldn't you agree?",
